repository-code: "https://github.com/JVLegend/smartsepsis"
url: "https://smartsepsis.vercel.app/"
abstract: >
  SmartSepsis-Oph is an AI-first computational design program for CRISPR-based
  point-of-care diagnostics targeting ophthalmic infections — endophthalmitis,
  microbial keratitis, and ocular surface infections. The pipeline produces
  CRISPR-Cas12a guide-RNA libraries, isothermal RPA primer designs, in silico
  specificity analyses, and functional variant scoring for resistance-gene
  families relevant to ocular microbiology. As of this release the program is
  in Phase 0 (computational design); experimental validation is pending.
keywords:
  - CRISPR-Cas12a
  - point-of-care diagnostics
  - antimicrobial resistance
  - ophthalmology
  - endophthalmitis
  - AI-first design
  - guide-RNA design
